      <div class="faq-block" id="can-i-pause-or-freeze-my-account-and-retain-my-developer-when-i-return">
        <h3 class="mt-16 mb-8 text-4xl text-gray-900 faq-question font-bold">Can I pause or freeze my account and retain
          my developer when I return?</h3>
        <div class="text-xl text-gray-900 faq-answer">
          <p>
            Yes, if you wish to pause your billing and want to return in the future and have us retain the same
            developer who you were assigned, we can do that with a reduced monthly fee.
          </p>
          <p>
            To reserve your Full-time developer (8-hours per day), the cost is $250/week.
          </p>
          <p>
            To reserve your Part-time developer (4-hours per day), the cost is $125/week.
          </p>
          <p>
            To reserve your Full-time developer (2-hours per day), the cost is $65/week.
          </p>
          <p>
            If you are canceling or pausing for just a few days or one-week, oftentimes that is short enough where we
            can reserve your developer without much issue or need for additional charges. However, if you plan on
            pausing for more than a few days, you would need to pay the retainer fee to lock in the same developer and
            time slot when you return again.
          </p>
          <p><a href="#top" class="text-gray-500 back-to-top font-bold hover:underline">Back To Top</a></p>
        </div>
